---
import CodeBlock from './CodeBlock.astro';
---

<section class="py-24 space-y-32 container mx-auto px-4">
    <!-- Header -->
    <div class="max-w-4xl fade-in">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-bold text-white mb-8 leading-none">
            AI Agent <br>
            <span class="text-blue-500">Sandboxing</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-slate-400 font-mono tracking-tight leading-relaxed border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-6">
            A guide to orchestrating high-velocity AI agents using the Bare Hub infrastructure. 
            Maximize agent autonomy while protecting your primary development environment.
        </p>
    </div>

    <!-- 01. Why Sandbox? -->
    <div class="fade-in space-y-12">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <span class="text-blue-500 font-bold text-2xl">01</span>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white tracking-wide">Why Sandbox?</h2>
        </div>
        
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 text-slate-400 text-sm">
            <div class="space-y-4 p-6 bg-slate-900 border border-slate-800 rounded-xl">
                <h4 class="text-white font-bold uppercase">No Collisions</h4>
                <p>AI agents often make massive, sweeping changes. In a worktree, these changes are isolated. Your main `git status` remains clean.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="space-y-4 p-6 bg-slate-900 border border-slate-800 rounded-xl">
                <h4 class="text-white font-bold uppercase">Parallelism</h4>
                <p>Run three different agents on three different bugs simultaneously. Each has its own physical directory and process space.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="space-y-4 p-6 bg-slate-900 border border-slate-800 rounded-xl">
                <h4 class="text-white font-bold uppercase">Safe Context</h4>
                <p>Agents won't see your uncommitted experiments or sensitive local files that aren't part of the branch history.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- 02. Deployment Protocol -->
    <div class="fade-in space-y-12">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <span class="text-blue-500 font-bold text-2xl">02</span>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white tracking-wide">Deployment Steps</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-16">
            <!-- Step 1 -->
            <div class="space-y-6">
                <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                    <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded bg-blue-500 flex items-center justify-center text-white font-bold">1</div>
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">Initialize the Sandbox</h3>
                </div>
                <p class="text-slate-400 max-w-2xl">Create a dedicated worktree for the specific ticket or task. This ensures the agent has a clean, branch-specific slate.</p>
                <CodeBlock code={`# Create a new worktree at ../agent-fix for a specific feature
git worktree add ../agent-fix -b ai/fix-issue-123
cd ../agent-fix`} label="Shell" />
            </div>

            <!-- Step 2 -->
            <div class="space-y-6">
                <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                    <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded bg-blue-500 flex items-center justify-center text-white font-bold">2</div>
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">Engage the Agent</h3>
                </div>
                <p class="text-slate-400 max-w-2xl">Launch your AI tool within the sandbox directory. The agent now has exclusive access to this isolated environment.</p>
                <CodeBlock code={`# For Claude Code
claude "Fix the layout bug in Header.astro"

# For Gemini CLI
gemini-cli "Refactor the authentication middleware"`} label="Shell" />
            </div>

            <!-- Step 3 -->
            <div class="space-y-6">
                <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                    <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded bg-blue-500 flex items-center justify-center text-white font-bold">3</div>
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">Review & Merge</h3>
                </div>
                <p class="text-slate-400 max-w-2xl">Once the agent finishes, review the changes in the sandbox. If satisfied, commit and push, or merge into your primary branch.</p>
                <CodeBlock code={`git add .
git commit -m "ai: fix layout bug"
git push origin ai/fix-issue-123

# Clean up the workspace
cd ..
git worktree remove agent-fix`} label="Shell" />
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- 03. Multi-Agent Orchestration -->
    <div class="fade-in space-y-12">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <span class="text-blue-500 font-bold text-2xl">03</span>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white tracking-wide">Multi-Agent Orchestration</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-slate-900_20 p-10 rounded-xl border border-slate-700">
            <p class="text-slate-300 mb-8 leading-relaxed">
                The Bare Hub excels when managing multiple agents. Use a naming convention for your sandbox directories to maintain clarity.
            </p>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
                <div class="p-6 bg-slate-900 rounded-xl border border-slate-800">
                    <h4 class="text-blue-400 font-bold mb-3">Concurrent Audit</h4>
                    <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mb-4">Run a security audit agent and a performance audit agent at the same time.</p>
                    <ul class="text-xs font-mono text-slate-400 space-y-1">
                        <li>üìÅ audits/security</li>
                        <li>üìÅ audits/performance</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="p-6 bg-slate-900 rounded-xl border border-slate-800">
                    <h4 class="text-blue-400 font-bold mb-3">Ticket Pipeline</h4>
                    <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mb-4">Assign separate tickets to separate agent instances.</p>
                    <ul class="text-xs font-mono text-slate-400 space-y-1">
                        <li>üìÅ tasks/fix-nav</li>
                        <li>üìÅ tasks/update-docs</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- 04. Pro Tips -->
    <div class="fade-in space-y-12">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <span class="text-slate-400 font-bold text-2xl">04</span>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white tracking-wide">Pro Tips</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
            <div class="border-l-2 border-blue-500 pl-6 py-2">
                <h4 class="text-white font-bold mb-2">Automate Node Installs</h4>
                <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm">Use a `post-checkout` Git hook in your `.bare` engine to automatically run `pnpm install` when a new worktree is created.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="border-l-2 border-blue-400 pl-6 py-2">
                <h4 class="text-white font-bold mb-2">Shared Build Cache</h4>
                <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm">Configure your build tools (Turborepo, Nx) to use a global cache so agents don't waste time rebuilding components you've already compiled.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
